[DOCUMENT]
TITLE: Stakeholder Requirements
UID: DOC-STK-REQ
VERSION: 0.1

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
Stakeholder (mission/task) level requirements: what the platform must
accomplish for its operators, independent of how the software is structured.
Each STK requirement is realized by a capability package
(docs/capabilities/CAP-*.md) that defines the operational concept, target
architecture, and gap to the current system. System requirements deriving
from an STK requirement carry a Parent relation to it.

STK requirements are validated (does the platform accomplish the task?), not
just verified — acceptance criteria live in the COMMENT field and the
capability's validation plan.
<<<

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Survey & Mapping

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: STK-1
STATUS: Approved
TAGS: capability, mapping
TITLE: Post-Flight 3D Survey Mapping
STATEMENT: >>>
The UAV shall fly a survey mission over an operator-defined area and deliver,
post-flight, a complete georeferenced 3D reconstruction of that area built
from the visual data collected during the mission.
<<<
RATIONALE: >>>
Photogrammetric mapping (terrain models, damage assessment, site surveys) is
a primary operator task for the platform alongside ISR. "Complete" means the
operator does not have to re-fly the area to fill holes.
<<<
COMMENT: >>>
Acceptance criteria (validation, see CAP-001):
(a) reconstruction covers >= 95% of the operator-defined survey polygon;
(b) ground sampling distance <= 5 cm at the surveyed altitude;
(c) map product available <= 2 hours after landing on the reference
    ground-station hardware;
(d) no manual intervention between dataset offload and map product.
<<<

[[/SECTION]]
